# Gameplay Mechanics

These rules apply to all levels and game modes.

## Energy Bar Drain

- Energy **does not drain** until the player starts moving (first directional input or jump).
- While the player is **moving** (holding left/right), energy drains at the normal rate (`ENERGY_DRAIN`).
- While the player is **standing still** (no directional input, on ground), energy drains at a significantly reduced rate (`ENERGY_DRAIN_IDLE`, roughly 25% of normal).
- Jumping and ducking count as "active" — once the player has started moving, the timer is active.
- This gives players time to read the HUD and orient themselves at the start of each level.

## Enemy Visual Style

Enemies use **solid fills with bold 3px outlines** matching `mockups/enemies-hazards-transparent.html`. They are distinct, visible threats — not translucent. Sprite backgrounds are transparent; the enemies themselves are opaque with clear outlines.

## Clouds

Clouds are always **fully opaque** (`alpha: 1`), not translucent.
